      • sendFile

        public SingleResult sendFile(String token,
                             Integer account,
                             String user,
                             String password,
                             String base64,
                             String coin,
                             Integer test)
                      throws ApiException
        Send file hash to bitcoin blockchain Send an OP_RETURN transaction with a base64 encoded file and return the API id for the blockchain transaction.
        Parameters:
        token - a signed JWT token with the company privatekey. (required)
        account - API ID for Account where the coins must be spend. (required)
        user - API user name. (required)
        password - API user password. (required)
        base64 - base64 encoded file. (required)
        coin - the coin name - bitcoin/litecoin. (required)
        test - if test = 1 so use testnet else test = 0 for mainnet. (required)
        Returns:
        SingleResult
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body
